Super Eagles forward, Kelechi Iheanacho scored his second goal for Leicester City as they went through to the quarterfinal of the Carabao Cup in Tuesday. Leicester City secured a 3-1 win over Burton Albion at the Pirelli Stadium. It was goals from Iheanacho, Youri Tielemans and James Maddison that secured a win for Brendan Rodgers’ side. Iheanacho who made his first start of the season and gave The Foxes the lead on 7 minutes. The Nigerian international scored against Luton Town in the third round. Also last night, Nigeria-eligible striker Josh Eppiah scored a brace to help Leicester City to a 2-1 victory over Grimsby Town in the Leasing.com Trophy at Blundell Park. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.